# Styling

## Stack

SCSS compiled to `public/dist/style.css`. Entry point: `src/styles/style.scss`.

Build: `npm run sass:build` (or `npm run build` which includes it).
Watch: `npm run sass:watch` (runs alongside NestJS via `npm run start:dev`).

## File Organisation

```
src/styles/
  style.scss        ← entry; @use or @forward partials only
  partials/         ← feature partials (_bands.scss, _albums.scss, etc.)
  plugins/          ← third-party overrides
```

- Prefix partial filenames with `_`.
- Use `@use` / `@forward` (not deprecated `@import`).

## Authoring

- BEM naming where it aids clarity; no deep nesting (max 3 levels).
- Variables and mixins defined in dedicated partials, not inline.
- Avoid inline styles in Pug templates; add a class instead.
- This project uses legacy SCSS ported from the original site — match existing conventions before introducing new patterns.
